this graduate student faq is a resource for current and new graduate students at sjsu. its six sections, "general", "admissions", "academic planning/ enrollment", "advancement to candidacy", "jobs/internships", and "culminating experience" are meant to serve as an easy-to-use guide to answer common questions.also refergraduate student handbookfor information regarding campus life, wellness, open university and special sessions.generaladmissionsconditional classification refers to your admission standing at sjsu and means that you have not satisfied all the required conditions for admission. the gape office provides you a letter which specifies the conditions being placed on your admission. you are not allowed to take more than 12 units of graduate courses until the conditions are satisfied. after you have satisfied all of the required conditions, you will need to fill out achange of classification in graduate program form [pdf] [pdf]and submit to yourgraduate program advisorto change your status.classified status indicates that you have satisfied all of the conditions of admission.it depends on the program you are applying to. please check the gape website for test requirements by college and programhere.conditional admission requires that your conditions are satisfied. if you have any prior coursework that might be similar and/or have any questions about your conditions, please contact yourprogram advisorto receive guidance.tuition fees and other fees for graduate students can be found under thebursar's office website.for questions about admission deferral to a graduate program,please check this webpageby the admissions' office.check out the steps to enrollment and who to contact if you have questionshere.yes, it is currently called ms in quality assurance, but there is plan to rename it to ms in engineering technology in the near future.academic planning/ enrollmentadvancement to candidacyyou may obtain the candidacy form from thegape forms site.you will need to be in classified status in your program, have earned at least 9 units of letter-graded courses, have fulfilled the gwar, and be in good standing to file youradvancement to candidacy petition.you will need to file a request for course substitution to substitute a core or an elective course listed on the candidacy form. you can find this online request underformson the gape website.jobs/internshipsinternship work during the fall and spring semesters is limited to 20 hours per week maximum for international students via thecurricular practical training (cpt)program. full-time work hours are possible while on cpt during the summer term. if you have completed all your program coursework except your culminating experience, talk to an isss advisor to see if you are eligible for and interested in early option post-opt or pre-opt.full-time work for international students on cpt is allowed during the summer term. you can alsowork on campusduring that time of the year if your schedule allows.check with an isss advisorif you have specific circumstances to consult on.culminating experienceyour culminating experience is aproject or a thesisat the graduate level. a culminating experience form is required by the university to show that you have met the necessary skills to obtain an ms degree. the form is processed by the graduate advisor after you have passed the project or thesis course successfully and your final report has been approved by your graduate committee.please reach out to yourprogram advisor/department mailbox for program specific questions.monday through friday, during business hours (closed weekends and holidays)visit office: virtually or in person at eng 116undergraduate:success-engineering@sjsu.edugraduate:graduate-engineering@sjsu.eduappointments with advisors:spartan connectphone: 408-924-3990all online courses at sjsu are delivered throughcanvas.monday through friday (except weekends and holidays), hours depending on location.: see our calendar forvirtual/drop-in hours: engineering 1st floor eng 116monday through friday8:30 a.m. to 12:00 noon1:00 p.m. to 4:30 p.m.(closed for lunch daily 12:00 - 1:00)in-person drop-in calendarsan jos state universityone washington square,san jos, ca 95192-0220